snippet.textDisplay: True Story: Dr. Seon (Dave's Mom) was my neighbor about 15 years ago in Cheverly, Maryland.  She lived alone so I would check on her from time to time.  One day she told me that people who usually tried to help/be nice to her was because of her son.  I had no idea who her son was because I had no real idea of who she was.  When I finally asked her who her son was she said, "Who is the number one comedian in America today?"  I quickly blurt out: You're Chris Rock's Mama?  She shot me a dumbfounded look and said, "no, THE OTHER ONE" 😂😂.  Congrats Dave, you are still winning in life.

The man, the legend. Also someone who understands and respects our great Constitution and the foundation on which it was created. This man understands far more about what makes this country great than most of the entertainment industry. He took a risk standing for more than just himself, but for country as well. And it paid off because the majority of Americans stand with his views. Right to free speech and supporting the 2nd if the 1st fails and of course, every amendment thereafter.

This man will go down in history as a legend not giving a FUCK, what anyone else thinks. And I also credit his mother for that. What a powerful woman shaping and molding the man that Dave is today.

This man understands far more about what makes this country great than most of the entertainment industry. He took a risk standing for more than just himself, but for country as well. And it paid off because the majority of Americans stand with his views. Right to free speech and supporting the 2nd if the 1st fails and of course, every amendment thereafter. 

This man will go down in history as a legend not giving a FUCK, what anyone else thinks. And I also credit his mother for that. What a powerful woman shaping and molding the man that Dave is today.
